"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-olympics-opening-ceremony-route-map-seine-paris-b2585777.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The river will feature prominently to kick off the Paris Games  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  A bold, uniqueopening ceremonywill kick off the ParisOlympicswith a tour along the River Seine.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organisers havepromised to deliver a compelling spectacleto accompany the 6km journey through the French capital on Friday.\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.980183933858656, \"rank\": 0.017948012334283184, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several hundred dancers and musicians will perform on bridges and along the riverbank too, offering an artistic show aimed at unitingFrance's diverse culture.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With this being the first opening ceremony to be held outside a stadium, organisers are keen to showcase Parisian landmarks.\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower, Notre-Dame Cathedral and the Louvre Museum are among the iconic buildings that will be on display in an event which is expected to last around three hours.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tour will begin at the Austerlitz Bridge next to the Jardin des Plantes (Botanical Gardens), while the L\\u00e9na Bridge, situated next to the Trocad\\u00e9ro Palace, will signify the end of the boat trip.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Austerlitz Bridge  Jardin des Plantes (Botanical Gardens)  Notre-Dame Cathedral  Louvre Museum  Eiffel Tower  L\\u00e9na Bridge  Trocad\\u00e9ro Palace  Organisers hope to show that the Olympics is not off limits for anyone, in tune with theParis 2024slogan, \\\"Games Wide Open\\\".\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 600,000 people will be in attendance, with an estimated 1.5 billion viewers around the world watching the television broadcast, which starts at 6.30pm BST.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.19083661010519e-14, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People who wished to be a part of the experience had the opportunity to apply for a free ticket from the 222,000 given out.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 100 boats will commence their journey at the Austerlitz Bridge and carry as many as 10,500 athletes along the city's main aquatic artery.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Significant changes have been made to allow the river-based opening ceremony to take place, as the upper and lower quays running alongside the Seine - where spectators will be placed - have been closed to the general public during preparations.\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2144, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7045441559208918e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greater measures to ensure people's safety have been introduced in France's capital, with local authorities installing an anti-terrorism barrier along the riverbanks while also carrying out more security checks by searching residents and commuters.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9668130096518901, \"rank\": 0.03415991100131976, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boots on the ground have been increased, too, with around 2,000 private security staff and 45,000 police officers expected to patrol the city.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers will be deployed on top of buildings along the route, coupled with a cutting-edge anti-drone system to ensure that any terrorist threats are suppressed.\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Should they wish to roam freely along the riverbanks, spectators and local residents need to carry permits on a QR code.\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the inconvenience that this has caused the people of Paris, city officials hope to unite the capital with a diverse and memorable representation of French culture.\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 3096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2986, \"end\": 2991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.688170745656008e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3081, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"BBC One is screening the Olympics opening ceremony from 5.45pm until 10pm on Friday 26 July  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3098, \"end\": 3105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5373746453307187e-17, \"text\": \"BBC One\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\"}, {\"begin\": 3242, \"end\": 3253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2653246327452826e-13, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"